    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The juvenile justice system, founded on the idea that childhood is a distinct stage of life, is being dismantled, with more teenagers imprisoned alongside adults. The ''tough on crime'' side has won, but what kind of society has resulted? A report by Margaret Talbot in The Times Magazine.</p>
      </block>
